<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Brazil's Burti Joins Jaguar Team </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, September 7 (Xinhua) -- Formula One outfit Jaguar have
signed Brazilian Luciano Burti to drive for them next season
alongside Ulsterman Eddie Irvine, the team announced in Monza,
Italy on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The 25-year-old test driver takes over from Johnny Herbert
after making his Formula One debut during the Austrian Grand Prix
when Irvine was too ill to race.
</P>
<P>
"Since I began my career in karting when I was 16, I have
worked towards one day driving in Formula One," said the Brazilian.
"I am delighted that it has happened but the important thing now
is to take this opportunity and contribute to the success of the
team," said Burti.
</P>
<P>
Burti finished third on the Formula Vauxhall circuit in 1996,
before joining the Paul Stewart team in British Formula Three,
finishing second in the 1999 championship. 
</P>
</TEXT>
