<HEADLINE> Four High-powered Canadian Teams to Visit Sydney Olympics </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
OTTAWA, September 7 (Xinhua) -- Canadian Prime Minister Jean
Chretien's wife, Aline, and three cabinet ministers are set to
lead four government delegations to the Olympics in Sydney, the
Ottawa Citizen newspaper said on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Leading one delegation, Ms. Chretien is registered to arrive at
the Games next week, while three other teams will be headed
respectively by Canadian Heritage Minister Sheila Copps, Sport
Minister Denis Coderre and Transport Minister David Collenette,
who is Chretien's political minister for Toronto bidding to become
the site for the next summer Olympics.
</P>
<P>
Canada's Olympic Ambassador David Adams is also expected at the
opening ceremony, the report added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
