<HEADLINE> FM Spokesman on U.S. Refusal of Issuing Visas to Yugoslav Delegates </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 7 (Xinhua) -- As a country where the United
Nations millennium summit is held, the United States is duty bound
to issue visas to delegates from Yugoslavia, a UN member country,
Foreign Ministry spokesman Sun Yuxi said here today.
</P>
<P>
Sun made the remarks when asked to comment on the U.S. refusal
to grant visas to major Yugoslavian delegates to the summit.
</P>
<P>
Yugoslavia is entitled to send a delegation to the summit, and
excluding and isolating Yugoslavia goes against the aim and
principle of the UN Charter, he stressed. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
