<DOCNO> XIE20000908.0014 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-09-08 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> South African Youth Called to Fight AIDS </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, September 7 (Xinhua) -- South African Deputy
President Jacob Zuma on Thursday challenged youth to be active in
the fight against spread of HIV/AIDS.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at an AIDS awareness campaign, Zuma said over the past
few years government had used every conceivable method to
highlight the dangers of the killer disease.
</P>
<P>
He said he believed the government's HIV/AIDS awareness
campaign had been highly successful, what remained was "for us to
break the AIDS chain".
</P>
<P>
"This can only be done by individuals like yourselves and like
myself taking responsibility for our own lives. I always liken HIV/
AIDS to an invading army and when an invading army attacks, it
aims to destroy," Zuma said.
</P>
<P>
"Therefore in our fight against HIV/AIDS, we must defend
ourselves and our country. We must fight back, defend ourselves
and chase away the enemy," he stressed.
</P>
<P>
"You must also be active in convincing those who still do not
believe that HIV/AIDS exists that indeed it is a serious threat
and that it kills. That is the task that I give you today," he
said.
</P>
<P>
"You are called upon to become activists once again and help
eradicate HIV/AIDS in the same manner that the youth of years gone
by helped rid our country of apartheid," Zuma added.
</P>
<P>
Zuma also discouraged youth from sexual activity until they are
old enough. 
</P>
</TEXT>
