<HEADLINE> UAE Boosting Adult Education </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ABU DHABI, September 8 (Xinhua) -- The United Arab Emirates
(UAE) is engaged in boosting adult education as part of its efforts
to stimulate the country's development.
</P>
<P>
On the occasion of the International Literacy Day on Friday, UAE
Education Ministry announced that the adult education centers will
be increased from 108 to 113 in the new academic year, with 39 for
men and 74 for women.
</P>
<P>
Mohammed Abdul Rahim Al Banna, director of the Adult Education
Department of the Education Ministry said adult students can reach
24,404 from 16,553, the official news agency WAM reported.
</P>
<P>
Minister of Education and Youth Ali Abdul Aziz Al Sharhan said
that the 108 adult education centres last year helped the adult
students complete their studies or eradicate illiteracy.
</P>
<P>
UAE Education Ministry has enacted a Federal Law, calling for
spreading education at all stages and work to reach each citizen in
the country, in conformity with the national literacy programs till
2020.
</P>
<P>
"To confirm that, the literacy programs and adult education have
been given special care and a lot of efforts conducted by the
ministry in cooperation with various organizations," the minister
said, adding that education is a basic element for community
development. 
