Blair attacked what he called a "one-size-fits-all mentality"
of comprehensives, and called on them to become more flexible to
be able to offer pupils personalized provision.
</P>
<P>
Addressing the two-day Progress 21st Century conference held in
Bedfordshire, England, Blair hailed education as still being Labor
's highest policy priority in the long term.
</P>
