specialist schools in England by September 2003 -- out of a total
of 3,500 schools -- offering advanced teaching in languages,
technology, sports and arts.
</P>
<P>
The two-day Progress 21st Century conference will also debate
the knowledge economy, social justice, the community, reinventing
government and Britain's new role in the world.
</P>
<P>
The Progress initiative was established by a group of Labor
Party activists in 1996 to promote dialogue between the leadership
and party members. 
