<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Zambia to Pay More Attention to Adult Education </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Community Development minister Dawson Lupunga said in Lusaka on
Friday that illiteracy levels, which tallies with the poverty
level at 70 percent, have greatly retarded economic growth and
development in Zambia.
</P>
<P>
The minister was speaking at the international literacy day
celebrations whose theme was "An hour of learning for every adult,
" here.
</P>
<P>
He noted that though there are some factors that have hindered
the literacy program such as low publicity and inadequate funding,
the program has however scored achievement as in learning and high
enrollment of women participation.
</P>
<P>
"Adult literacy is one way we can reduce the poverty levels and
it would also help to foster development in the country," he added.
</P>
<P>
Lupunga further said adult literacy would empower women to
control their lives and therefore, break free from the bone of
poverty.
</P>
<P>
The minister called for more concerted efforts from both
government and the cooperating partners and further urged the
cooperating partners and other stakeholders to come and fight
illiteracy in the country.
</P>
<P>
And speaking earlier, the United Nations Educational,
Scientific and Cultural Organization (UNESCO) country
representative Cheikh Ndiaye said illiteracy is a major stumbling
in Africa, adding that governments should therefore focus their
attention on literacy issues and needs in order to reaffirm the
importance of literacy to society.
</P>
<P>
Ndiaye said unless it is given adequate human and financial
resources, literacy cannot make a significant impact.
</P>
<P>
He added that significant and sustained improvement would not
be possible unless literacy programs are designed to change
prevailing norms and attitudes that keep women and girls
uninformed, insecure dependent and overburdened.
</P>
<P>
Ndiaye congratulated teachers, non-Governmental Organizations (
NGO's)and other stakeholders in Zambia for their tireless efforts
in combating illiteracy. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
