<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Russia Arrests Aide to Chechen Rebel Leader </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, September 8 (Xinhua) -- Russia said Friday that it has
arrested a top aide to Chechen rebel leader Arbi Barayev.
</P>
<P>
Kharon Yunusov, the 35-year-old chief of staff of notorious
Chechen field commander Barayev, was arrested in Moscow in late
August, the Interfax news agency reported, quoting a spokesman for
the Russian Interior Ministry's main anti-organized crime
department.
</P>
<P>
The department received information that Yunusov, who was
allegedly involved in numerous abductions and combat operations
against federal forces for Barayev's band, was to arrive in Moscow
to visit his nephew in a local hospital.
</P>
<P>
Yunusov was arrested while leaving the hospital on August 28
and a hand grenade was seized from him.
</P>
<P>
Yunusov, charged with illegal possession of arms, is now being
held in a Moscow detention center. Investigation into his
involvement in illegal bandit formations is also being conducted,
Interfax said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
