<BODY>
<HEADLINE> India Urges Global Strategy Against Poverty </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, September 8 (Xinhua) -- India said on Friday
that in a globalized economy, poverty eradication cannot be
treated as the exclusive responsibility of individual nations.
</P>
<P>
Addressing the U.N. Millennium Summit which opened at the U.N.
headquarters in New York on Wednesday, India's Prime Minister
Bihari Vajpayee said it should be the concern of all humanity and
a new global strategy against the poverty is essential.
</P>
<P>
Another universal concern is the debt burden of many developing
nations, which grows yearly with new debt being contracted to pay
off current interest charges, the prime minister said.
</P>
<P>
This results in a continual hemorrhage of wealth that further
debilitates the developing world, the prime minister noted.
</P>
<P>
"The United Nations has a signal role to play in this global
efforts: by focusing attention on equitable development, by
ensuring that development is not the preserve of a few," he said.
</P>
<P>
"It is time that we looked at assurance of economic development,
growth and distribution together in a high-level U.N. conference,"
he said.
</P>
<P>
The prime minister urged that development be made a cross
cutting issue in the work of a reformed United Nations. 
</P>
</TEXT>
