<HEADLINE> 721 Cases of Pipeline Vandalization Recorded in Nigeria </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, September 8 (Xinhua) -- A total of 721 incidents of
pipeline vandalization, 82 of which resulted in explosions, have
so far been recorded across the country this year, the News Agency
of Nigeria reported on Friday.
</P>
<P>
The figures were released by Joe Oduocha, manager of government
and community from the Nigeria National Petroleum Corporation, at
a workshop on pipeline vandalization in the capital Abuja on
Thursday.
</P>
<P>
He appealed to the local communities to help the government
check vandalization of oil pipeline which caused loss of lives and
property and environmental devastation.
</P>
<P>
Nigeria is the biggest oil-producing country in Africa with
output of more than two million barrels a day, but residents in
the oil-producing areas complained they benefited little from oil
revenues. 
</P>
</TEXT>
