<DATE_TIME> 2000-09-08 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Nigeria Reiterates Support for Angola's Peace Efforts </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUANDA, September 8 (Xinhua) -- Nigeria will continue to
support the Angolan government for its efforts to restore peace
and stability in the country, a Nigerian diplomat said here Friday.
</P>
<P>
Nigerian ambassador to Angola Eheneden Erediauwa made the
remarks after a meeting with Joao Lourenco, secretary general of
the ruling People's Liberation Movement of Angola, who informed
the Nigerian ambassador of the recent development of the political
and military situation in Angola.
</P>
<P>
Erediauwa said that Nigeria is committed to help the Angolan
government realize peace after a 25-year civil war since
independence from Portugal in 1975.
</P>
<P>
"I expressed the will of Nigeria to work in close collaboration
with the Angolan government in political, social and economic
aspects," he said.
</P>
<P>
Considering that peace in Angola is vital for maintaining
stability in the southern African region, Nigeria has been always
supporting the efforts made by the Angolan government to end the
conflict and bring peace to the war-torn country, he added.
</P>
</TEXT>
