<HEADLINE> Greek Stocks Continue Upward </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATHENS, September 8 (Xinhua) -- Greece's equity prices
continued its upward tendency Friday with the general index on the
Athens Stock Exchange (ASE) rising 7.92 percent to 4,381.79 points,
its highest close since June.
</P>
<P>
The FTSE/ASE 20 index ended 9.07 percent at 2,511.99 points
while the FTSE/ASE 40 index finished 6.27 percent higher at 586.04
points.
</P>
