<HEADLINE> Canada's Jobless Rate Up to 7.1 Percent in August </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
OTTAWA, September 8 (Xinhua) -- Canada's unemployment rate rose
to 7.1 percent in August from 6.8 percent in the previous month,
Statistics Canada reported Friday.
</P>
<P>
About 1.14 million people were looking for jobs when only 9,000
positions were generated monthly since March, much less than the
average monthly growth of 44,000 positions in the preceding six
months.
</P>
<P>
There was little change in full-time job creation, with almost
all of the new jobs added to the economy being part-time.
</P>
<P>
Most of the jobs were created in the service and trade sectors,
while employment dropped in the goods-producing, hospitality and
construction sectors.  
</P>
</TEXT>
