<HEADLINE> Shanghai: Fascinating Destination for Foreign Experts </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, September 8 (Xinhua)-- With influx of some 30,000
foreign experts every year, there are about 100,000 foreign people
working in this largest economic and financial city in China now,
latest statistics indicate.
</P>
<P>
Over 70 percent of these people are working in nearly 20,000
foreign-funded enterprises as high-class managers. The rest of the
foreign experts are engaged in scientific research, cultural
development, publishing, education, health, media and other
sectors.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, Shanghai invites several hundred of foreign experts
on short-term work to deal with specific technical or management
problems.
</P>
<P>
The number of foreign people visiting Shanghai has continued to
increase since China initiated the reform and opening-up policy in
the late 1970s.
</P>
<P>
At first, the visitors mainly came from the former Soviet Union
and eastern Europe. Now, foreign experts from over ten countries
are playing an active role in developing Shanghai's industry,
finance, science and technology, commerce, consultation,
agriculture and education.
</P>
<P>
Now, foreign employees make up only one percent of Shanghai's
total population, much fewer than other metropolis in the world.
</P>
<P>
Experts estimated that there will be more foreign people coming
to Shanghai after China joins the World Trade Organization.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE20000908.0059 </DOCNO>
