<HEADLINE> Typhoon to Hit Hainan Island </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 8 (Xinhua) -- China's 16th tropical storm
for the year, Typhoon "Wukong", is reaching China's island
province of Hainan at a speed of 15 kilometers per hour.
</P>
<P>
Chinese Central Meteorological Station (CCMS) today raised the
alarm of the pending typhoon.
</P>
<P>
According to the CCMS, the typhoon was centralized at 18.8
degrees north latitude and 113.4 degrees east longitude at 2 p.m.
Beijing Time.
</P>
<P>
Under the influence of the typhoon, strong gale and rain storms
will hit South China Sea and the coastal area of south China's
Guangdong Province from tonight to tomorrow.
</P>
<P>
Hainan provincial government has announced the state of
emergency and has made all necessary preparations. 
</P>
</TEXT>
