<HEADLINE> 12 Pak Soldiers Killed in Shelling: India </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, September 8 (Xinhua) -- India claimed on Friday that
12 Pakistani soldiers were killed in escalated shelling along the
Line of Control (LOC) in Jammu and Kashmir since Thursday, while
three Indians, including two porters and an armyman, also lost
their lives.
</P>
<P>
Pakistani troops resorted to heavy shelling and small arms
firing along the LOC in a dozen sectors in Kashmir since Tuesday
night, the Press Trust of India (PTI) quoted local defense sources
as saying on Friday.
</P>
<P>
Three Indians were killed in Pakistani troops' shelling across
the border in Uri sub-sector on Thursday and five others were
injured in other sectors, said the PTI.
</P>
<P>
In retaliatory shelling by Indian troops on Pakistani positions
at Kunda and Juda sub-sectors, 12 Pakistani soldiers were killed
and many injured, Indian defense sources told the PTI.
</P>
<P>
The shelling continued throughout the night in some sectors and
the exchanges of fire were still continuing on Friday, the sources
added.
</P>
<P>
India claimed that Pakistan has escalated border shelling and
firing to push in a large number of armed militants into Jammu and
Kashmir. 
</P>
</TEXT>
