<HEADLINE> S. Korea to Make Draft Loans to Ease Transactions </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SEOUL, September 8 (Xinhua) -- South Korea's central bank will
provide intra-day draft loans to local commercial banks and
foreign bank branches in the country from late September to
smoothen settlements among them, said the Bank of Korea Friday.
</P>
<P>
Banks suffering temporary shortages of settlement funds will be
able to take out loans up to the average outstanding amount of
their reserve requirements deposited at the central bank.
</P>
<P>
The loans will carry no interest because they should be paid
back by the end of the business hours each day. 
</P>
