<HEADLINE> U.S. Machine Supplier Joins in Three Gorges Accident Investigation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YICHANG, September 8 (Xinhua) -- A representative from the U.S.
supplier of the machine which killed three workers and injuring 30
others started today his investigation at the construction site of
the Three Gorges Project.
</P>
<P>
Around 6:50 pm on September 3, workers from Gezhouba Company
Group were still working at the flood discharge section of the
gigantic water control dam when the No. 3 tower belt machine broke
from a height of 19.6 meters and collapsed, throwing down 29
workers who were working on the belt. Four other workers that were
working below the belt did not escape the disaster.
</P>
<P>
Immediately after the accident, representatives from Yangtze
River Three Gorges Project Development Corporation, Gezhouba Group
Company, and officials from relevant departments in Yichang, the
nearest city to the construction site, went to the site of the
accident in an effort to rescue workers.
</P>
<P>
The U.S. company also joined the investigation team, which will
examine the general condition of casualties, equipment and
technology, and the handling of the case.
</P>
<P>
Authoritative sources said Gezhouba Group Company has banned
the use of other tower belt machines and roof belt machines, while
concrete pouring at the flood discharge section has also
temporarily been stopped.
</P>
<P>
According to the previous plan, construction workers will have
poured 5.4 million cubic meters of concrete into the dam by the
end of this year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
