<HEADLINE> Long-March 4-B Rocket Succeeds in Three Launches </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, September 8 (Xinhua) -- A celebration was held today
in east China's Shanghai for the three successful launches of Long-
March 4-B carrier rocket, which sent a new earth resource
satellite into orbit on September 1.
</P>
<P>
The 45-meter-long rocket, developed by the Shanghai Aerospace
Administration, is an upgraded version of the Long-March 4-A. The
rocket was put into use in May 1999 and has sent four satellites
into space in two pervious launches.
</P>
<P>
The Long-March series rockets have been awarded by the State
Aerospace Administration for their good quality, reliability and
wide adaptability.
</P>
<P>
The Shanghai Aerospace Administration, one of China's research
bases of space technology, shoulders the development of carrier
rockets and application satellites. The administration also
participates in research of China's manned space shuttle program.
</P>
</TEXT>
