<HEADLINE> Motorola Aims to Be Best Investor in China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XIAMEN, September 8 (Xinhua) -- Motorola's top official in
charge of its China business today said that the company aims to
be the best foreign investor in China.
</P>
<P>
In an interview with Xinhua, P. Y. Lai, president of Motorola (
China) Electronics Ltd., said that the success made by Motorola in
China is a result from the Chinese government's well-advised
policy and the company's own strategic development plan.
</P>
<P>
Lai promised to further localize his company and greatly expand
its business in China.
</P>
<P>
The company, which had invested a total of 12.5 billion yuan (1.
5 billion U.S. dollars) in China up to July this year, will add
another 16 billion yuan (1.93 billion dollars) to build a world-
class semiconductor production base in Tianjin, north China.
</P>
<P>
An international telecommunications giant, Motorola invested 1.
3 billion yuan into a research academy in China with a total of 18
institutes and more than 800 research fellows.
</P>
<P>
In 1999, Motorola's China sales reached 26 billion yuan, with
its tax payment up to 2.8 billion yuan. Its 10.2-billion-yuan
exports made it that year's biggest exporter among foreign
companies operating in China. 
</P>
