<HEADLINE> GE Starts New Company in China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XIAMEN, September 8 (Xinhua) -- General Electric (GE) today
announced in Xiamen, east China's Fujian Province, that it will
start a new company which is responsible for running purchase and
export business in China.
</P>
<P>
The proposed company will provide consultation service for
product quality and related technologies, said Wang Jianmin,
president of GE (China) Co.
</P>
<P>
According to sources, the new GE company is the only solely-
funded service business run by multinationals in China.
</P>
<P>
"Our new company has received the go-ahead from the Chinese
government, which indicates China is starting to open its service
sector to foreign investors," Wang said.
</P>
<P>
Cheng Jiashu, general manager of the new company, estimated
that their turnover in the coming couple of years will exceed one
billion U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
GE now has more than 30 solely-funded and joint-venture
enterprises in China. The international giant is planning to
greatly develop purchase trade in the country. 
</P>
