<HEADLINE> Singapore Nabs 11 for Selling Pirated Goods </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, September 8 (Xinhua) -- The Singapore Police has
arrested 11 suspects for selling pirated goods during raids
conducted at various parts of Singapore on Friday.
</P>
<P>
More than one million Singapore dollars (about 580,000 U.S.
dollars) worth of pirated goods, including CD-ROMs, CDs and VCDs,
were also seized by the Police.
</P>
<P>
The raids were part of a police operation to smash a syndicate
involved in selling and distributing pirated goods.
</P>
<P>
The Policy said that investigations are still in the process
and more suspects are expected to be taken down. 
</P>
</TEXT>
