<HEADLINE> Moderate Earthquake Jolts Afghanistan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, September 8 (Xinhua) -- An earthquake of moderate
intensity measuring five on Richter scale jolted Afghanistan on
Friday morning, Associated Press of Pakistan (APP) reported.
</P>
<P>
Quoting a preliminary report of Meteorological Station Peshawar
(Pakistan), the report said that the earthquake originated at 0837
hours (local time) and its epicenter lied about 250 kilometers
North West of Peshawar in Afghanistan.
</P>
</TEXT>
