<HEADLINE> Malaysian E-Village Opened </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, September 8 (Xinhua) -- Malaysian Prime Minister
Mahathir Mohamad said the opening of Malaysia's Entertainment
Village marked the beginning of an exciting new entertainment era
and industry of the country.
</P>
<P>
The Prime Minister said what started as an idea has now
materialized into something tangible.
</P>
<P>
"E-Village is today a reality and we will pursue this till we
can stand alongside others in the entertainment industry
professionally and globally," he said when launching the E-Village
in Dengkil near here Friday.
</P>
<P>
He said it was also of great significance that Malaysians were
on the threshold of acquiring new knowledge and the necessary
technical know-how of managing the wonderful new electronic world
of entertainment.
</P>
<P>
"The development of E-Village and particularly the virtual and
Sound Studios clearly demonstrate our ability to keep up with, if
not be ahead of, a burgeoning information technology industry and
growing market," he said.
</P>
<P>
Mahathir said the E-Village project would witness a growth of
opportunities, both social and economic, the transforming of
society and the building of new creative skills and professions.
</P>
<P>
The Prime Minister said the vision to establish an
entertainment center went far beyond mere entertaining as it would
help in developing the skills and capacities to handle the modern
and fast changing technologies involved in entertainment in the
information age.
</P>
<P>
He expressed confidence that the development of E-Village would
set the right targets and goals of Malaysia to be not only an
industrialized nation but enlarge the boundaries to test and
challenge Malaysians to achieve more.
</P>
<P>
The Prime Minister said a whole new infrastructure would emerge
and the foundation of hi-tech entertainment would be laid, which
could then be further developed and generate revenue.
</P>
<P>
With the new resurgence of film making in the world, Mahathir
hoped E-Village would be the springboard for attracting
international film producers and providers of entertainment.
</P>
<P>
Mahathir said the local film industry would benefit from E-
Village as it would improve the standards and technics and become
comparable to those produced at other entertainment centers.
</P>
<P>
"I look forward to the day when our home grown films and other
international productions carry the credit mention of having being
produced in E-Village Studios Malaysia," he added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
