<HEADLINE> S. Korea, Russia Seek Cooperation in Atomic Energy </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SEOUL, August 8 (Xinhua) -- South Korea and Russia will enhance
cooperation in the field of atomic energy, according to the
Ministry of Science and Technology on Friday.
</P>
<P>
A four-member Russian delegation, which arrived here on
Wednesday, held talks with South Korean officials on Thursday,
focusing on strengthening security of radioactive materials and
reducing nuclear waste, the ministry said.
</P>
<P>
The two sides agreed to promote exchange of technology and
information on the next generation of liquid metal reactors, it
said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
