<HEADLINE> Economic, Trade Fair Ends in Northwest China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
URUMQI, September 8 (Xinhua) -- The eight-day foreign economic
and trade fair closed today in Urumqi, capital of northwest China'
s Xinjiang Uygur Autonomous Region.
</P>
<P>
Businessmen from home and abroad signed foreign trade contracts
worth 1.6 billion U.S. dollars, up 18.1 percent than last year.
</P>
<P>
Participants also signed 12.25 billion yuan-worth in deals
involving domestic trade and cooperation.
</P>
<P>
Overseas investors from Kazakhstan, Hong Kong and Saudi Arabia
showed great interest in cotton, tomato sauce and other products.
Trade with Japan, the Republic of Korea, Hong Kong and Russia
sharply increased due to the economic recovery in the countries
and regions after the financial crisis.
</P>
<P>
The Fair was first held in 1992 and foreign trade business
deals from the previous eight fairs amounted to about 12 billion U.
S. dollars. Deals involving internal trade and economic
cooperation between Xinjiang and other parts of the country were
47.5 billion yuan. 
</P>
