<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, September 8 (Xinhua) -- A total of 13 people were killed
and dozens wounded in road accidents over last two days in Turkey,
reported the Anatolia News Agency on Friday.
</P>
<P>
A bus carrying workers on Friday plunged on the shoulder of the
road in Manisa province, southwest Turkey, killing eight people on
the spot.
</P>
<P>
Three more died later after the more than 30 injured were rushed
to hospital for emergency treatment. Now there are still 26 people
in hospital.
</P>
<P>
On Thursday, a truck collided with a military vehicle on a
highway in the southern Adana province, killing two soldiers and
wounding another two.
</P>
<P>
The truck driver, who was also wounded, was taken into custody
for causing the fatal accident.
</P>
<P>
Turkey has long suffered from fatal traffic accidents. Over the
past 10 years, such accidents claimed 60,000 lives and seriously
injured or disabled 1 million people, according to official
figures. 
