<DATE_TIME> 2000-09-08 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> New Tanzanian Port Opened to Boost Trade in Great Lake Region </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, September 8 (Xinhua) -- A new dry port has been
opened in northwestern Tanzania to facilitate trade for countries
in the Great Lake region, the independent Guardian newspaper
reported here on Friday.
</P>
<P>
The opening of the Isaka Dry Port on Thursday is aimed at
significantly reducing cargo-handling time from the current over
14 days to about five days, Fuad Abdallah, the Tanzania Railways
Corporation (TRC) Principal Commercial Manager, was quoted as
saying.
</P>
<P>
TRC had bought two 45-ton front loaders and built two
warehouses to convert the Isaka container terminal into the
current dry port, which has a container stacking area able to keep
360 twenty-foot containers at a go.
</P>
<P>
With a capacity of handling 42,000 tons of break-bulk cargo and
13,000 twenty-foot containers annually, the Isaka port will be
able to effectively handle goods bound to and from the three
landlocked countries of Burundi, Rwanda and the Democratic
Republic of the Congo (DRC), Abdallah said.
</P>
<P>
The conversion project is intended to make the port a viable
gateway for the three countries' sea-borne trade by using a road
to Dar es Salaam 502 kilometers shorter than the existing "
northern corridor," which runs through Kenya to its coast city of
Mombassa.
</P>
<P>
Commercial sectors in the three countries have hailed the
project, anticipating that it will help reduce consumer prices by
cutting 40 percent of transportation costs. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE20000908.0108 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-09-08 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Tourism Picks up in Kenya's Port City of Mombasa </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, September 8 (Xinhua) -- Tourism has picked up by 75
percent in Kenya's tourist resort Mombasa since the high season
started in July this year, Mombasa Mayor Masoud Mwahima has said.
</P>
<P>
The East African Standard newspaper on Friday quoted Mwahima as
saying that the city council was working on "missions and visions"
in the next six months for a conducive environment to boost the
tourism industry.
</P>
<P>
Mwahima said Thursday that nice climate and clean and beautiful
beaches along the Indian Ocean made Mombasa a tourist attraction.
</P>
<P>
Mombasa, one of the most famous tourism attractions in the east
Africa, has lured thousands of Europeans each year.
</P>
<P>
The mayor also appealed to foreign investors to lay more
emphasis on Kenya to help it recover from the current economic
hardship.
</P>
<P>
"We are trying to create the right environment for investment,"
said Mwahima.
</P>
<P>
Signs of recovery have been shown in Kenya over the past two
years after it suffered from a sharp decline in tourism in 1990s.
</P>
</TEXT>
