<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Cathay Pacific Gets Record Monthly Passenger Figure </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, September 8 (Xinhua) -- Cathay Pacific Airways, Hong
Kong's leading air carrier, registered a new monthly record of 1,
085,533 passengers in July, surpassing its previous record of 1,
030,456 set in April this year.
</P>
<P>
In a press release issued Friday, the airlines said that in the
first seven months of the year, it carried a total of 6.84 million
passengers, 16.1 percent more than the 5.89 million carried in the
comparable period last year.
</P>
<P>
The passenger load factor rose to 83.3 percent in July, up from
77.4 percent in June. For the year to date, the passenger load
factor has risen to 76.8 percent, eight percentage points higher
than in the first seven months of 1999.
</P>
<P>
Cargo has also continued to see strong market demand with a
total of 423,082 tonnes carried by the end of July, a growth of 16
percent over the same period in 1999, the press release said.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
