<DOCNO> XIE20000908.0167 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-09-08 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Europe's Energy Resource Should Be Diversified: EU Commissioner </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, September 8 (Xinhua) -- European Union (EU) Commissioner
of Energy Loyola de Palacio said on Friday that Europe should
revise its policy of transport and diversify its energy resources.
</P>
<P>
In an interview with the radio France Inter, De Palacio said
that the blockade of oil refineries and roads and "blackmail of
society" by French truckers and farmers are unjustifiable.
</P>
<P>
"One cannot take hostage the whole productive sectors of the
neighboring countries," she said. "I see in a very very negative
way the actions which are going on in France."
</P>
<P>
She admitted that Europe is disarmed in the face of the rise of
oil prices in world market and said she will propose in October "a
communication on the security of energy supply" to the 15 EU
member countries.
</P>
<P>
The EU Commission will propose the revision of transport policy
of EU countries, including a shift from road transport to railway
transport, she said.
</P>
<P>
The commissioner also said that Europe should not abandon its
nuclear energy, which she said can help the continent fend off
shocks from future oil crises. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
