<DATE_TIME> 2000-09-08 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Europe Has No Means to Pressure OPEC, Says French Oil Group </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, September 8 (Xinhua) -- The president of the French oil
group Total-Fina-Elf, Thierry Desmarest, said on Friday that
Europe does not have the necessary means to pressure the
Organization of Oil Exporting Countries (OPEC) to increase
production.
</P>
<P>
In an interview with the LCI television channel, Desmarest said
that the means of intervention of European countries is "extremely
limited."
</P>
<P>
"The Americans have no doubt a little more of political-
military influence than Europe, and they tried for several months
to do the same (make OPEC increase production) without success,"
he said.
</P>
<P>
He also said that the present situation in the world oil market
does not make up an "oil shock."
</P>
<P>
"Taking into the account of inflation, the price of 32 U.S.
dollars per barrel today makes up only half of the prices we had
at the beginning of the 1980s," he said.
</P>
<P>
The oil price jumped above 35 dollars a barrel Thursday evening
in New York, the highest in 10 years.
</P>
<P>
OPEC will decide whether to increase its production or not when
its member countries meet in Vienna on September 10.
</P>
<P>
The United States and European Union have called on OPEC to
increase production by around one million barrels a day. 
</P>
</TEXT>
