<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Eximbank Provides Credit for Ghana Electrified Project </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 8 (Xinhua) --The Export and Import Bank of
China (Eximbank) signed an export seller's credit contract today
with China International Water &AMP; Electric Corp (CWE) to provide
162 million yuan (about 19.28 million U.S. dollars) and 6.4
million U.S. dollars for a project in Ghana, which has been
contracted by the CWE.
</P>
<P>
This is China's first export credit project in Western Africa.
The contract values 32.82 million U.S. dollars, which will be
supported by Eximbank's credit with an outstanding term of 11
years.
</P>
<P>
All the electronics and machinery products for the project will
be made in China, a spokesman for Eximbank said.
</P>
<P>
He said that the Eximbank has engaged in a number of successful
business ventures with the CWE involving contracting large
projects overseas.
</P>
<P>
As the State's major export credit institution, the Eximbank has
used many financial tools including export loans, export credit
insurance and foreign-oriented guarantees to support the export of
machinery and electronics equipment, complete sets of equipment
and high-tech products. 
</P>
</TEXT>
