<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China's Bond Market Slumps </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 8 (Xinhua) -- China's T-bond market
continued to drop as the rally at stock market drew funds out of
the bond market today.
</P>
<P>
Half of the bonds listed on the market dropped, according to
Homeway, China's leading on-line financial and securities advisory
company.
</P>
<P>
Transaction value continued to contract to 1.55 billion yuan,
80 million yuan less than the total on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The floating rate ten-year bond due 2007 plummeted 0.57 percent
to end at 103.80 yuan, with the yield rising to an all-time-high
of 2.49 percent.
</P>
<P>
The average price on China's repurchasing market plunged amid
heavy trading. The combined repurchasing transactions totaled 7.88
billion yuan, down 234 million yuan from Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The interest rate of the 3-day repurchasing agreement fell from
4.9 percent to 2.4 percent. 
</P>
</TEXT>
