<HEADLINE> China's Fund Market Friday </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 8 (Xinhua) -- China's securities investment
fund market spent the last trading day of the week consolidating
Thursday's gains Thursday as 12 of the 30 funds listed on the
market remained unchanged.
</P>
<P>
Twelve funds rose and six declined Friday, according to Homeway,
China's leading on-line financial and securities advisory company.
</P>
<P>
Heavy trade of Fund Jinghong, a discounted fund, helped push
the market higher. Fund Jinghong saw a turnover of 52.44 million
units.
</P>
<P>
Homeway said that the lower-than-value prices of the discounted
funds had drawn interest from investors. 
</P>
