<HEADLINE> Shenzhen A-Shares Up </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 8 (Xinhua) -- The Shenzhen Composite Index
wound up the week's trade by rising 2.28 points to 603.93 points
on Friday.
</P>
<P>
The sub-index closed at 4701.05 points, up 30.58 points or 0.38
percent from the last close, according to Homeway, China's leading
on-line financial and securities advisory company.
</P>
<P>
Turnover totaled 7.54 billion yuan, 6.2 percent less than 8.04
billion yuan on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The Shenzhen A-share market opened 0.17 points higher at 602.35
points and managed to climb higher despite an intraday slump to
599.98 points. The sub-index opened 10.68 points higher at 4681.5
points today.
</P>
<P>
Homeway predicts that the Shenzhen A-share market will continue
to go up next week. 
</P>
