<HEADLINE> Shanghai B-share Market Review </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 8 (Xinhua) -- The Shanghai B-share market
stopped losing ground and consolidated as investor sentiment
improved this week, according to Homeway, China's leading on-line
financial and securities advisory company.
</P>
<P>
The Shanghai B-share index rallied 5.49 points or 8.51 percent
to 69.97 points at the close of trading this week, slightly off
its weekly high of 70.10 points.
</P>
<P>
The index rose above the 70-point bar for the first time in
September on Friday.
</P>
<P>
The 5-day turnover contracted to 104.80 million U.S. dollars,
47.39 million U.S. dollars less than the total of last week.
</P>
<P>
Bargain hunting by investors helped to push the market higher
this week following continuous decline over the previous two weeks.
</P>
<P>
Revised optimism about the long-term performance of the stock
market encouraged investors to hold their stakes in the B-share
bourse.
</P>
<P>
Homeway predicts that the Shanghai B-share market is likely to
lose some of the ground gained next week. 
</P>
</TEXT>
