<HEADLINE> UNESCO Personnel Visit Thailand </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, September 8 (Xinhua) -- A group of personnel of the
United Nations Educational Scientific and Cultural Organization (
UNESCO) is visiting Thailand for a study mission of key agencies
in the country, including the state-run Mass Communication
Organization of Thailand (MCOT), the Thai News Agency (TNA) said
Friday.
</P>
<P>
The September 3-10 visit to Thailand of the UNESCO personnel is
part of the U.N. organization's staff exchange program, aimed to
strengthen ties and understanding among UNESCO member states.
</P>
<P>
The UNESCO personnel from Japan, China, and South Korea are
scheduled to visit key agencies and organizations in Thailand,
both in Bangkok and other provinces, under its framework of
cooperation in the fields of education, science, culture, and mass
media.
</P>
<P>
The group visited the MCOT on Thursday to study work and
projects of the state-run organization's key structure, including
Thai News Agency (TNA), TNA Radio News Channel FM100.5 MHz, and T.
V. Channel 9, as well as the organization's advanced information
technology structure, which provides variety of on-line news and
information to serve the public and media agencies. 
</P>
