<HEADLINE> Tokyo Share Prices Rebound </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, September 8 (Xinhua) -- Stock prices rebounded in Tokyo
Friday, helped by bargain-hunting, with the benchmark Nikkei index
closing higher for the first time in nine trading days.
</P>
<P>
The Nikkei Stock Average of 225 selected issues on the First
Section of the Tokyo Stock Exchange rose 201.09 points, or 1.23
percent, from Thursday's close at 16,501.55.
</P>
<P>
The broader-based Tokyo Stock Price Index (TOPIX), covering all
First Section issues, jumped 23.59 points or 1.59 percent to 1,509.
88.
</P>
<P>
Turnover on the major section increased to 907.10 million
shares from Thursday's 544.50 million shares, with Nippon Steel as
the day's volume leader.
</P>
<P>
Semiconductor makers gained in response to Thursday's upturn in
New York's Nasdaq composite index. Gainers included the drug,
telecom and brokerage sectors, while the rubber sector was weak.
</P>
<P>
Of the issues listed on the First Section, gainers outpaced
losers 859 to 389, while 170 issues closed unchanged. 
</P>
