<HEADLINE> Kuerten to Take Part in Sydney Olympics </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SYDNEY, September 8 (Xinhua) -- Brazilian tennis ace Gustavio
Kuerten will take part in the Olympic Games after his sponsors
Diadora and the Brazilian Olympic Committee (COB) resolved a
dispute about what he should wear at the Games.
</P>
<P>
According to local reports, Kuerten, double French Open
champion, said that he would set off today to join the Brazilian
team in Sydney.
</P>
<P>
He withdrew from the Brazilian team on Tuesday after the COB
refused to agree to his sponsors Diadora's demands that he should
not wear the logo of a rival.
</P>
<P>
Kuerten said the COB had now agreed he could play in a kit
displaying neither his own sponsor's name nor that of the
Brazilian team sponsors.
</P>
