<HEADLINE> State Councilor Says Coming Decade Crucial For China (Details) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XIAMEN, September 8 (Xinhua) -- The coming five to ten years
will be an important period of economic and social development for
China, said State Councilor Wu Yi today in Xiamen, east China's
coastal province of Fujian.
</P>
<P>
She made the remark in a speech titled "An Open China with
Brilliant Future" at the Fourth China Fair for International
Investment and Trade.
</P>
<P>
"We are to simultaneously embark on the retracking of economic
system, restructuring of the economy and the transformation of
economic growth modes, which will further improve the relationship
between demand and supply, economic structure and institutional
pattern," said Wu.
</P>
<P>
The two-decade reform, opening-up and rapid development has
enabled China to consolidate its comprehensive national strength.
People's life has improved considerably, its international status
has been on the rise and it has reached the strategic objectives
set by the first and second step of modernization drive, she said.
</P>
<P>
Wu pointed out that China's economic development will be
highlighted in several aspects. The strategic adjustment of
economic structure will be accelerated, she said.
</P>
<P>
She said China will work hard to accelerate the
informationization of its national economy and society and bring
the industrial structure and quality to a new level. The country
will also make headway in urbanization, change existing structure
of the city and countryside and bridge the gap between them.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, the strategy of Developing West China will be
implemented while the advantages of China's eastern regions will
be given to play as before so that the eastern, central and
western regions can five impetus to one another and develop in a
coordinated manner, she said.
</P>
<P>
By deepening reform, State-owned enterprises will set up modern
corporate system, enforce stockholding system and participate in
market competition as real players who are responsible for their
own management decisions, profits and losses.
</P>
<P>
The effort, she said, will fortify the status of public
ownership as the mainstay.
</P>
<P>
The strategy of Rejuvenating the Nation through Science and
Education will be further implemented, she said. Science,
technology and education will make greater progress and following
reform in these aspects, integrate closely with economic
construction.
</P>
<P>
To go with the trend of scientific and technological
development of today's world, she said China will accelerate the
establishment of State Scientific and Technological Innovation
System to increase the capability of making scientific and
technological innovations and turn the scientific achievements
into practical productivity.
</P>
<P>
Wu noted China will also nurture professionals in various
sectors, improve the quality of labor force and actively create
incentive mechanism and social environment that helps excellent
talents find way to distinction. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
