<HEADLINE> Ugandan Coffee Exports Down in August </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, September 8 (Xinhua) -- Ugandan coffee exports dropped
by 24.3 percent to 220,302 bags at the end of August from 291,029
bags recorded in the previous month, according to the latest
report of the Uganda Coffee Development Authority (UCDA).
</P>
<P>
The report available Friday revealed that corresponding export
earnings declined by 29.6 percent to 9.47 million U.S. dollars
compared with 13.45 million dollars earned in July.
</P>
<P>
The exports in August represented a drop of 27.5 percent from
303,987 bags over the same period last year.
</P>
<P>
The drop in coffee exports was mainly attributed to very low
prices on the world market, which forced exporters to scale down
their volume. The average crop price dropped to 0.72 U.S. dollar
in August from 0.77 dollars in July this year.
</P>
<P>
Coffee export is the major foreign exchange earner of the east
Africa country, accounting for about 60 percent of the country's
total foreign exchange earnings. 
</P>
</TEXT>
