<HEADLINE> Cause of Traffic Accident in Ningxia Made Clear </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YINCHUAN, September 8 (Xinhua) -- Illegal overtaking was the
main cause of a major traffic accident that occurred on a section
of the No. 312 state trunk highway in Ningxia Hui Autonomous
Region, last Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The traffic accident claimed the lives of 14 people and injured
27 others. Thirteen of the 42 passengers aboard a bus operated by
a transport company in Yongcheng City of Henan Province were
killed instantly, and one died on the way to a local hospital. All
the injured passengers were sent to local hospitals.
</P>
<P>
The refitted sleeper bus, which carried 42 passengers including
37 people of Uygur ethnicity, crashed into a cliff near a tunnel
at Liupan Mountain after it was hit by a truck, which was
attempting to overtake the bus.
</P>
<P>
Wang Yufa, driver of the truck, has surrendered himself to the
police and is being investigated.
</P>
<P>
After the accident, a 140-member rescue team was formed to get
the victims to hospital. Relevant departments in Guyuan Prefecture
are communicating with Xinjiang Uygur Autonomous Region and Henan
Province on the aftermath of the accident.  
</P>
