<HEADLINE> China Leads Developing Countries in Foreign Investment </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Addressing the Fourth China Fair for International Investment
and Trade, which opened today, Shi Guangsheng, Minister of Foreign
Trade and Economic Cooperation, said that as of July this year,
China has approved more than 353,000 foreign-invested enterprises,
involving a contractual investment of 641.7 billion U.S. dollars
and actual funds of 327.7 billion dollars.
</P>
<P>
Shi disclosed that during the January-July period this year,
newly-approved enterprises with foreign investment and the
contractual volume of FDI recovered and began to grow.
</P>
<P>
A total of 11,891 foreign-investment enterprises obtained
approval to set up, climbing 26.9 percent year-on-year, with a
contractual investment of 27.64 billion dollars, up 24 percent
over the same period last year.
</P>
<P>
A marked increase was also reported in imports and exports
during the 7-month period, with the volume being 257.6 billion
dollars, 36.3 percent higher than that for the same period of 1999.
Of the total number, exports surged by 35.8 percent and imports,
by 36.8 percent, producing a trade surplus of 14.34 billion
dollars.
</P>
<P>
Shi said that China's achievement in economic development is
inseparable with the policy of opening-up and the importance its
government attaches to the economic and trade cooperation with
various countries and regions in the world.
</P>
<P>
China will always be open to the outside world, accelerating
its reform and creating more favorable conditions for investment
cooperation in the new century.
</P>
<P>
Shi noted that to adapt to the world scientific and
technological progress, and the speeding up of the economic
globalization, China will strategically adjust its economic
structure, deepen its reform in economic systems and open wider to
the outside world.
</P>
<P>
He urged both Chinese and overseas investors to pay more
attention to the new growth areas of the Chinese economy, from
which they can find new opportunities for development. 
</P>
</TEXT>
