<HEADLINE> State Councilor Meets Macao SAR Chief Executive </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Wu said that she is glad to see that Macao's economy is slowly
recovering in less than one year after it returned to the
motherland.
</P>
<P>
She said that the Central Government is very concerned about
economic development in Macao.
</P>
<P>
She added that she believes that the Macao people, under the
leadership of Ho, will continue to carry out the principles of "
one country, two systems," "Macao people governing Macao," and a
high degree of self-government.
</P>
<P>
Wu said that the Macao people will surely be united and make
efforts for the prosperity of the motherland.
</P>
<P>
Wu noted that the total economic and trade volume between the
mainland and Macao amounted to 472 million US dollars in the
January-July period, up 32 percent from a year earlier.
</P>
<P>
Ho expressed his thanks to the Central Government for the
support it has given to Macao SAR.
</P>
<P>
He said the economy in Macao is expected to grow next year.
</P>
<P>
Wu also exchanged views with members of the Macao business
delegation on developing economic and trade cooperation between
the mainland and Macao. 
</P>
</TEXT>
