<HEADLINE> Another 150 White Farms in Zimbabwe Gazetted for Acquisition  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, September 8 (Xinhua) -- The Zimbabwean government
gazetted another 150 white commercial farms for compulsory
acquisition Friday, bring the total number of identified farms to
2,102.
</P>
<P>
A preliminary notice was published by Minister of Lands,
Agriculture and Rural Resettlement Joseph Made Friday when the
Commercial Farmers' Union (CFU) was preparing to take the
government to court over the acquisitions.
</P>
<P>
The CFU said, at its annual congress that ended here Thursday,
that it would challenge the constitutionality of the compulsory
farm acquisitions.
</P>
<P>
The government intends to acquire 3,041 white farms to resettle
landless families through the fast-track resettlement program.
Owners or other interested parties of the farms mentioned in the
notice have been given a month to respond. 
</P>
