<HEADLINE> Two Officials Refused Entry by Australian Authorities </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SYDNEY, September 8 (Xinhua) -- Two officials were denied entry
by Australian authorities for the pending Olympic Games, including
a Uzbekistan National Olympic Committee member.
</P>
<P>
Francois Carrard, IOC director-general, on Friday asked
Australian Prime Minister John Howard to shed the light on why the
two accredited officials for the Sydney Games were denied entry.
</P>
<P>
Under the rules of the International Olympic Committee,
accreditation for the Games acts as a visa for the host country.
</P>
<P>
"We have asked for an explanation for the reasons," said
Carrard, who declined to give the identity of the two people
involved.
</P>
<P>
However, he still revealed that one was a representative of an
international sporting federation and the other was a National
Olympic Committee official.
</P>
<P>
