<DATE_TIME> 2000-09-08 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China's Opening-Up to Enter a New Phase </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XIAMEN, September 8 (Xinhua) -- China's opening-up will enter a
new phase as the process of WTO accession speeds up, said Wu Yi,
China's State Councilor, here today.
</P>
<P>
Wu made the remark in her speech titled "An Open China with a
Brilliant Future" when addressing the Fourth China Fair for
International Investment and Trade (CFIIT), which opened here this
morning in Xiamen, a special economic zone in southeast China's
coastal province of Fujian.
</P>
<P>
Wu noted that the new phase is reflected by various aspects.
</P>
<P>
First of all, she said, the opening-up will be expanded from a
restricted scope and areas to all-round openness.
</P>
<P>
"And the opening-up permitted by policy featuring experimental
nature will be changed into predictable opening-up under legal
framework, namely, to open up in accordance with committed
schedule," said Wu.
</P>
<P>
The unilateral opening-up mainly on the Chinese side will be
turned into mutual opening between China and WTO members, the
senior Chinese official said.
</P>
<P>
In order to comply with the WTO rules, she said, China is
screening and modifying the existing foreign-related economic laws
and regulations and establish foreign trade and economic
cooperation administrative system consistent with international
conventions and China's national conditions.
</P>
<P>
"According to the commitments China has made to other countries
and the need of its own national economic development," Wu said, "
we shall make unremitting efforts to improve the level of opening-
up and participate in the process of economic globalization in a
more active gesture and even wider scope." 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE20000908.0242 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-09-08 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China to Utilize More Foreign Investment, Wu Yi (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XIAMEN, September 8 (Xinhua) -- China will unswervingly pursue
the reform and opening-up, stick to the principle of utilizing
foreign investment in an active, rational and effective way no
matter what happens to international situation.
</P>
<P>
The remark was made today by State Councilor Wu Yi at a
luncheon of the Fourth China Fair for Investment and Trade in
Xiamen, a booming special economic zone in southeast China.
</P>
<P>
In her speech "An Open China with Brilliant Future", Wu hailed
it a meaningful way to jointly study the role and development
trend of international direct investment in the process of
economic globalization, explore new approaches to consolidate
international investment cooperation, and look into the prospect
of China's foreign investment attraction.
</P>
<P>
It is an important component of China's fundamental state
policy of opening-up to absorb foreign direct investment (FDI),
she said.
</P>
<P>
China's foreign investment has kept increasing in the past 20-
odd years.
</P>
<P>
According to Wu, China has accumulatively approved
establishment of more than 350,000 foreign-funded firms with a
total contractual capital of 641.7 billion U.S. dollars and actual
investment of over 327.7 billion U.S. dollars by the end of July
of this year.
</P>
<P>
"From 1993 to 1999, China has been the developing country
absorbing the largest amount of foreign capital seven years in a
row," she said.
</P>
<P>
She recalled that after the outbreak of the Asian financial
crisis, international capital fled away and China was inevitably
affected to some extent.
</P>
<P>
However, many foreign investors have come back again, which is
indeed heartening for the Chinese people, she said.
</P>
<P>
The active utilization of foreign capital has not only promoted
the sustained, sound and swift development of the Chinese economy,
in particular its economic restructuring and industrial upgrading,
but also provided to the vast number of international investors
precious business opportunities and enormous marketplace, she said.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE20000908.0243 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-09-08 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China to Utilize More Foreign Investment, Wu Yi (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The achievements of China's foreign investment attraction
should be attributed to the political stability, social security
and relatively high speed of economic development, she added.
</P>
<P>
Besides, China has gradually summed up some mature practices
after the exploration. The practices including:
</P>
<P>
-- Enriching and improving laws, regulations and policies
related to foreign investment attraction on a consistent basis
while enhancing the efficiency and service of government agencies
so as to create better environment for foreign investment.
</P>
<P>
-- Gradually expanding the opening-up of service industrial and
protecting in real earnest the legitimate rights and interests of
foreign investors, treating each other as equals and providing
mutual benefit in the course of common development.
</P>
<P>
In today's world, she said, economic globalization has become
a historical trend that is irresistible.
</P>
<P>
"China is absorbing foreign capital as necessitated by its
economic development, which also contributes to the international
investment collaboration," Wu added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
