<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China to Accelerate Reform Process of Marketization </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Shi Guangsheng, Minister of Foreign Trade and Economic
Cooperation, made this remark at the Fourth China Fair for
International Investment and Trade, which opened in the port city
of Xiamen today.
</P>
<P>
He said the Chinese government will take more forceful measures
to further open the market for trade in goods and trade in
services.
</P>
<P>
China will, according to the WTO rules and its commitments in
bilateral agreements, enhance legal construction and intensify the
revising of policies and regulations on foreign investment in a
step-by-step and planned manner to improve the transparency of
policies and regulations, and further perfect the legal system for
foreign investment.
</P>
<P>
China will continue to reinforce law enforcement on
intellectual property right protection, quicken the exercise of
national treatment to foreign-invested enterprises (FIEs) and
protect the legitimate rights and interests of FIEs and its
laborers in accordance with law through the improvement of
legislation and intensified law enforcement, he said.
</P>
<P>
He noted that the Chinese government will conduct
administration according to law, strengthen management and exert
itself to set up a clean and highly-effective administrative
system. 
</P>
</TEXT>
