<DOCNO> XIE20000908.0256 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-09-08 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Thailand Joins ASEAN Telecom Network </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, September 8 (Xinhua) -- Thailand has cooperated with
other five countries of the Association of Southeast Asian Nations
(ASEAN) in launching ASEAN's first comprehensive telecommunication
network, the Thai News Agency (TNA) reported on Friday.
</P>
<P>
Transport and Communications Minister Suthep Thuegsuban
presided over a launch ceremony at the Asia Comm/ExpoComm 2000
Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The network is based on the integration of multi-
telecommunication approaches, including the Internet, the
International Private Leased Circuits, the Frame Relay Service,
the Very Small Aperture Terminal Service (VSAT), and the Video
Conference Service.
</P>
<P>
The integration was the development and application of an
automatic teller machine (ATM) network to be linked to other
telecommunication networks in form of multi-media, with high speed,
security and reliability, said Suthep.
</P>
<P>
ASEAN has linked its telecommunication network comprehensively,
based on the advanced ATM system so that members can communicate
quickly, safely, and reliably through the regional multi-media
integrated telecommunication system, he stated.
</P>
<P>
The integrated telecommunication system could also cope with
expansion and changes of technologies in the future, he noted.
</P>
<P>
ASEAN member countries joining in the comprehensive
telecommunication network include Brunei, Indonesia, Malaysia, the
Philippines, Thailand, and Singapore. 
</P>
</TEXT>
