<HEADLINE> Sri Lankan Police Raid Illegal Money Printing Press </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, September 8 (Xinhua) -- Sri Lankan police have raided
an illegal money printing press in the North Western Province,
seizing 800,000 rupees (10,190 U.S. dollars) worth of forged note,
police sources said Friday.
</P>
<P>
During the raid on Thursday at Dummalasuriya, some 70
kilometers north of Colombo, the police were able to arrest the
owner of the business and two operators who were printing forged
money, said the sources.
</P>
<P>
The police also seized a computer, laser printing machine and
some passports and identity cards which are believed to have been
forged.
</P>
<P>
The raid was conducted by the local police who, acting on a tip-
off, had taken two persons into custody with 20 pieces of 1,000
rupees (12.7 dollars) counterfeit notes earlier on Thursday.
</P>
