<HEADLINE> Forest Parks Flourish in Guangzhou </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
GUANGZHOU, September 8 (Xinhua) -- Guangzhou in south China's
Guangdong Province has 16 forest parks, the biggest number in all
provincial capitals in China.
</P>
<P>
As a regional political and economic hub, Guangzhou has forest
covering 41.5 percent of the city area, or 224,000 ha. The city
spends over 10 million yuan (1.2 million US dollars) annually on
tree planting.
</P>
<P>
Local forest parks combine landscape gardens and amusement
grounds with stone-laid walk-ways through woods. The refreshing
environment and convenient infrastructure have made local forest
parks very popular.
</P>
<P>
The Liuxihe National Forest Park, the first one in the city,
received 700,000 tourists last year earning 15 million yuan (1.8
million US dollars) in revenue.
</P>
<P>
Another eight forest parks are planned to be built by 2002,
which will increase the coverage of forest parks to 60,000 ha.,
accounting for 7.8 percent of the city area. 
</P>
</TEXT>
