<HEADLINE> Over 100 People Killed in Fires in Romania This Year </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUCHAREST, September 7 (Xinhua) -- A total of 119 people were
killed and 244 others were injured in some 11,000 fires across
Romania in the first eight months of this year, Romania's
firefighting forces said here Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Firefighters rescued 1,125 people and saved property worth more
than 1.3 billion leu (about 56,500 U.S. dollars), Emil Marinescu,
chief of staff of the firefighting forces, told a press conference.
</P>
<P>
In January-August, the number of fires rose by 87 percent
compared with the same period of last year.
</P>
<P>
Prolonged drought over the past several months and
unprecedented high temperatures in the summer this year were
mainly responsible for the frequent fires.
</P>
<P>
In the eight-month period, 539 forest fires occurred in the
country, five times that of the same period in 1999, destroying
539 hectares of forest. Forty-five percent of the forest fires
were caused by improper use of fire by tourists, he added.
</P>
<P>
To prevent fires, the fire fighting forces have stepped up the
implementation of preventive measures in buildings and
institutions in the country. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
