<HEADLINE> Food Risks to Be Investigated in L.America </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HAVANA, September 7 (Xinhua) -- The United Nations World Food
Program (WFP) is undertaking investigations on food risks in 11
Latin American countries, a WFP official said here Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The WFP's regional delegate, Italian Paolo Mattei, told a press
conference that the analysis basically records food risks due to
natural causes and the ability to respond to the problems.
</P>
<P>
The WFP official explained that Latin American countries,
especially those in the Caribbean and Central American zones, have
to declare themselves in a state of emergency practically every
year, as a consequence of cyclones, earthquakes, drought or other
natural disasters.
</P>
<P>
Mattei highlighted the investigation in five eastern Cuban
provinces, which he said was the most detailed analysis carried
out by the WFP in the region.
</P>
<P>
The investigations are carried out in different phases, in Peru,
Ecuador, Colombia, Bolivia, Nicaragua, Honduras, El Salvador,
Guatemala, Haiti, the Dominican Republic and Cuba.
</P>
<P>
The reports are delivered to their respective governments as a
methodological tool of action to fight hunger. 
</P>
</TEXT>
