<HEADLINE> L.America Has 40 Million Illiterates </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUENOS AIRES, September 7 (Xinhua) -- About 40 million people
are illiterate in Latin America, of which 50 percent live in
Brazil, a U.N. official said here Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Juan Carlos Tedesco, a representative of the U.N. Fund for
Education, Science and Culture (UNESCO) in Argentina, said that of
the other half, 80 percent are indigenous to Mexico, Bolivia, Peru,
Ecuador and Guatemala.
</P>
<P>
He said literacy programs at a technical level are much more
complex among natives, because they must work with their distinct
languages, many of which are not written languages.
</P>
<P>
Tedesco also said that among people under 20 years old, few are
illiterate because of great advances in schooling. 
</P>
