<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Picasso Artworks on Display in Vienna </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
VIENNA, September 7 (Xinhua) -- A collection of 104 works of
art by the Spanish master Picasso is on exhibit in Vienna.
</P>
<P>
One hour before the opening of the exhibition on Thursday, a
long queue formed in front of the Bank Aust ria Kunst, the
location of the exhibition.
</P>
<P>
According to organizers of the exhibition, this is the largest
and most comprehensive collection of Picasso's artworks ever
displayed in Vienna. More than 10,000 tickets have been sold in
advance.
</P>
<P>
Among the artworks are many pieces painted in Picasso's late
period, including oil paintings, sketches, and water colors.
Visitors can also appreciate, from this exhibition, the diversity
of this master's versatile art styles.
</P>
<P>
A highly-productive artist, Picasso left 35,000 pieces of art
to the world after his death in 1973, one-fifth of them to his
eldest son Paul, who gave them to his son, Bernard, Picasso's
grandson, after his death in 1995. The exhibit in Vienna is
primarily from Bernard's collection, with some of them seen by the
public for the first time.
</P>
<P>
Picasso was born in Malaga, Spain, in 1881. He was brought up
in a creative and artistic atmosphere because his father was a
painting teacher. Picasso moved to Paris in 1904 after his early
academic training in art in Spain; he gradually became an
established artist in Paris. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
