<HEADLINE> Central American Trade Ministers to Meet on Free Trade Pact </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
PANAMA, September 7 (Xinhua) -- Central American Ministers of
Trade will meet on Sunday in Washingtron to analyze a Free Trade
Agreement (FTA), a Panamanian Minsitry of Trade and Industry
official announced Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The Ministry Official, Joaquin Jacome, said that the leaders
of trade of Central American countries will study obstacles in FTA
negotiations between Panama and Central America, which have
advanced 50 percent until now.
</P>
<P>
Talks regarding FTA have taken place on four occasions, after
Mireya Moscoso's Panamenian adminstration preferred a free trade
agreement with Central America after assuming power on September 1,
1999.
</P>
<P>
The fifth round of FTA talks will be carried out in October in
El Salvador.
</P>
<P>
Former Vice Foreign Trade Minister Roberto Henriquez recently
predicted that if talks regarding FTA fails to come through by end
of year 2000, the agreement may collapse. 
</P>
</TEXT>
