<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Beijing's Machinery, Electrical Equipment Trade Up </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 8 (Xinhua)-- The export value of machinery
and electrical equipment in Beijing reached 1.28 billion U.S.
dollars in the first seven months of this year, up 93.2 percent
from the same period last year, latest statistics from Beijing
Customs show.
</P>
<P>
The import value of such products during the same period
reached 2.94 billion U.S. dollars, increasing 30.5 percent from
the same period last year.
</P>
<P>
Overseas-funded enterprises exported some 1.01 billion U.S.
dollars of machinery and electrical equipment in the first seven
months, which was 80 percent of the city's total export of such
products.
</P>
<P>
Increased tax reimbursement for exports and preferential
policies for exporting software products have contributed to the
rapid growth of the machinery and electrical equipment trade.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, Beijing has expanded its original machinery and
electrical equipment markets in Hong Kong, Japan, the United
States, Europe, Latin America, Canada and Australia this year.
Europe has become Beijing's second largest market for Machinery
and Electrical Equipment. 
</P>
</TEXT>
