<HEADLINE> Nationwide Program to Develop Children's Potential </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HOHHOT, September 8 (Xinhua)-- China will launch a nationwide
education program to develop the potential of children in all
aspects.
</P>
<P>
Gu Xiulian, vice-chairwoman of the All-China Women's Federation,
declared recently that the "century children" plan will introduce
advanced educational methods from abroad to improve the
intelligence and capability of children, which is expected to
enhance the overall quality of Chinese people.
</P>
<P>
China has 367 million children, one quarter of the nation's
population. Many children bear heavy psychological and
physiological burdens caused by inappropriate schooling or
troubled family lives.
</P>
<P>
Children between the ages of 0 to 12 will be involved in the
program, which provides education on four stages and provides all-
round services during the whole process.
</P>
<P>
In addition to the "century children " plan, the federation
will continue to advocate network education and health education
programs for children in the future, according to Gu. 
</P>
