<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 20th Germany-sponsored Forest in Northwest China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XI'AN, September 8 (Xinhua)-- The 20th Germany-sponsored
forestation project in China has been launched in Yan'an, the
famous revolutionary base in northwest China's Shaanxi Province.
</P>
<P>
With 12 million marks (about 5.5 million U.S. dollars) from the
German government, China will plant 15,700 hectares of forest and
another 2,300 hectares of forest that yields economic earnings,
and consolidate some 18,000 hectares of farmland in nine years in
Yan'an.
</P>
<P>
China and Germany began to cooperate in forestation efforts
eight years ago. Since then, Germany has donated some 220 million
marks (about 100 million U.S. dollars) to China for forestation
purpose and Germany-aided forests have covered some 100 counties
and towns all over the country.
</P>
<P>
China started a large program to return cultivated land to
forests last year. Using overseas aid to plant more forests will
be another important way to protect the environment, said Quan
Zhichang, director of the local forestry office. 
</P>
</TEXT>
