<HEADLINE> Czech Airlines Shows Gains </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PRAGUE, September 8 (Xinhua) -- Czech Airlines made a profit of
382 million crowns (about 10 million U.S. dollars) in the first
seven months of this year after losses in the same period last
year, the Czech News Agency reported Friday.
</P>
<P>
In the January-July period of this year, the company carried
more than 1.3 million passengers and 9,100 tons of cargoes, which
increased by 22.2 percent and 33.8 percent respectively compared
with last year. In the mentioned period last year, it reported a
deficit of 158 million crowns (about 4.2 million dollars).
</P>
<P>
Vaclav Kral, vice president of the company, told a press
conference that the growth was attributed to the economic recovery,
the ending of Balkan conflict and the increasing foreign customer
demand.
</P>
<P>
Czech Airlines expects to post a net profit of 206 million
crowns (about 5.4 million dollars) this year.
</P>
<P>
Kral added that the company planned to add two Boeings 737-400s
to its fleet next year. Currently, it has a total of 28 different
kinds of planes. 
</P>
