<HEADLINE> Wall Street Stocks Fall Broadly on Corporate Profit Warnings </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, September 8 (Xinhua) -- Wall Street stocks fell
broadly Friday as investors took profits from a recent rally in
response to profit warnings from a number of companies.
</P>
<P>
The Dow Jones industrial average closed down 39.22 at 11,220.65
points, extending its loss of 50.77 points Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Broader stock indicators were mostly lower. The technology
heavy Nasdaq composite index fell 119.94 at 3,978.41 and the
Standard &AMP; Poor's 500 index fell 8.01 at 1,494.50.
</P>
<P>
The market fell after a handful of companies warned that their
earnings in the third quarter would not meet expectations. Among
them were Gadzoox Networks, First Data, MPower Communications and
automotive parts maker TRW.
</P>
<P>
Analysts from Morgan Stanley Dean Witter Corp. and Merrill
Lynch downgraded First Data and MPower Communications separately
after the two companies lowered their profit expectations.
</P>
<P>
Corporate profit warnings sparked worries among investors about
investment returns in the slowing U.S. economy. Traders cashed out
of some blue chip stocks and moved the money to the tech sector
Thursday after companies such as DuPont, Campbell Soup and Circuit
City Stores warned that they could not meet earnings expectations
in the third quarter. Blue chips fell while tech shares rose on
that day.
</P>
<P>
The Federal Reserve has raised interest rates for six times
since last summer in a preemptive move to cool off the economy and
keep inflation from rising. Rate hikes could lead to higher costs
and lower demands for companies.
</P>
<P>
The NYSE index rose 0.24 at 675.73. But the American Stock
Exchange index fell 6.26 at 967.92. The Russell 2000 index of
smaller companies fell 7.12 at 535.70.
</P>
<P>
Declining issues outnumbered advancers by a 5-to-4 margin on
the New York Stock Exchange, with 1,540 down, 1,325 up and 489
unchanged.
</P>
<P>
NYSE volume declined to 958.65 million shares from 973.54
million in the previous session. 
</P>
</TEXT>
